The paper discusses online supervised learning algorithms for sequence prediction problems and node classification in social networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), social and information networks (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses computational aspects of the proposed algorithms, which could also place it in the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE).
